Private and gated 1920's Tudor in Sunset Square. Remarkably remodeled with exquisite style best describes this no-excuse home. Nestled at the base of the historic Hollywood Hills and a block from the iconic Sunset Strip. Walk to the Chateau Marmont and all that West Hollywood and the Sunset Strip have to offer. This home is chic and sophisticated yet modern and luxurious. Gorgeous entry way with high cove ceilings, leads to the regal living room with fireplace and casement windows. Formal yet very open floor plan from the dining room to the gourmet kitchen that features custom cabinets & top of the line appliances. Upstairs you will find three large bedrooms, two with en-suite bathrooms, plus a third bathroom. Outdoors is a perfect setting to unwind with an entertaining seating area, grassy backyard and an oyster shell Bocce Ball court. Romantic outdoor dining for 10 with built-in kitchen. 2-Car garage + 4 more in gated drive. Perfect setup for an ADU conversion. Stellar property.

Nearby restaurants include The Counter, The Griddle Cafe and Zankou Chicken. 1546 N Fairfax Ave is near Wattles Garden Park, Trebek Open Space and Poinsettia Recreation Center.
